      <pb n="1"/>
        <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>May 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date></p>
        <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your favor has come<lb/> to hand in which I am glad to perceive<lb/> that you are satisfied with my proceeding<add>&#63;</add><lb/> in regard to the remaining Bibles<lb/> I shall make it my Business to see<lb/> those refusing once more.  I have to<lb/> say in regard to <persName>Mr Plahto</persName> that the<lb/> man is evidently a Lunatic and<lb/> I should not be surprised if in the<lb/> course of a little time he <sic>his</sic> known<lb/> for an our and out madman<lb/> relative to the remaining Tephilia<lb/> you can charge it to me at &#36;4.00<lb/> one of your subscriber for the Occident<lb/> <persName>John M Myers</persName> leaves here with his<lb/> family for <placeName>New York</placeName> on the <date>23d</date> of this month<lb/> you will have therefore to send to <placeName>New<lb/> York</placeName> to him I do not know if I<lb/> am call&#39;d upon to do this for I<lb/> thought it would save dispute and<lb/> also a member or subscribe you</p>
      <pb n="2"/>
        <p>can put down the Name of <persName>A. S Myers</persName><lb/> a a subscriber to the occident<lb/>  I presume from the commencement of this<lb/> present volume.  direct of course to this<lb/> city I sent you the name of <persName>J A Hart</persName><lb/> in my last I hope it will be att<add>&#63;</add> to</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Hoping you are well</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I subscribe myself</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">H Myers</persName></p>
        <p><placeName>Box 1515</placeName></p>
        <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>May 9&#47;54</date></p>
        <p>Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">At a meeting of the members<lb/> of the United Hebrew Congregation the secretary<lb/> was notified to send <sic>and</sic> advertisement to<lb/> the occident and also to the Asmonean<lb/> &#40;in the office of which you will oblige me<lb/> by sending a copy for publicity&#41; stating<lb/> that the United Hebrew Congregation are in<lb/> want of a talented person to fill the<lb/> office of Preacher and Lecturer he must<lb/> be versed in the German as well as the<lb/> English Language the Congregation will<lb/> pay for such services the sum of one<lb/> thousand dollars pr annum as we are<lb/> in want of a proper school for the<lb/> purpose of teaching our children in the</p>
      <pb n="3"/>
        <p>faith of our Fathers it would be <add>&#63;</add><lb/> that the person applying should have<lb/> the <sic>neccessary</sic> qualifications to start a<lb/> school and to superintend if necessary<lb/> this as a matter of course would<lb/> <sic>argument</sic> his Salary.</p>
        <p>All letters to be address to the<lb/> secretary <persName role="author">H Myers</persName> <placeName>Box 1515 St Louis<lb/> Mo</placeName></p>
        <p>Bills for advertising &#38;c &#38;c sent<lb/> to your office<lb/> if there is any other Jewish<lb/> Journals besides the two above<lb/> mentioned you will please send<lb/> notice and charge to me</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">H Myers</persName></p>
      <pb n="4"/>
        <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
